1.Story

Singapore has a new milestone of becoming a zero-waste nation as government is worried about the rising number of waste disposal. At the current pace, the Semakau Landfill will run out of space by year 2035 which is an alarming situation for Singaporeans (towardszerowaste.gov.sg). Making matters worse, Singapore has limited land for building new incineration plants or landfills. The government would like to motivate citizens by sharing the total energy that the combined recycling efforts have saved every year.

2.Scenario

We have 3 data file which contain: 1. The energy_saved file gives the amount of energy saved in kilowatt hour (kWh) and the amount of crude oil (barrels) by recycling 1 metric tonne (1000 kilogram) per waste type 2. Waste Data 2003 to 2017 3. Waste data 2017 to 2020

The goal is to tranformed the data from 3 existing files into below table:

We will be using R to calculate energy saved every year from 2015 to 2019 based on five waste types: plastics, paper, glass, ferrous and non-ferrous metal.

5.Transform Data

5.1 Data for the year 2015 to 2017

However, we just need data from 2015 onwards, and, the waste type must be on the list, waste_0317 is transformed:

waste_1517 <- waste_0317 %>% 
filter(year %in% c(2015:2017))

waste_1517 <- waste_1517 %>%
  filter(waste_type %in% c('Plastic','Plastics','Ferrous metal','Glass','Non-ferrous metal','Paper/Cardboard','Non-ferrous metals'))

waste_1517 <- waste_1517%>% 
  select(waste_type, year, recycled =total_waste_recycled_tonne )

Trim the data:

waste_1517 <- waste_1517 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_to_lower(waste_type))

waste_1517 <- waste_1517 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_replace_all(waste_type,"paper/cardboard", "paper"))

waste_1517 <- waste_1517 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_replace_all(waste_type,'non-ferrous metals',"non-ferrous metal"))

waste_1517 <- waste_1517 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_replace_all(waste_type,'plastics', 'plastic'))

5.2 Data for 2018 to 2019

Retrived columns needed for the analysis

waste_1819 <-  waste_1819 %>%
  select(waste_type=`Waste Type`, year=Year, recycled=`Total Recycled ('000 tonnes)`)

waste_1819 <- waste_1819 %>%
  filter(waste_type %in% c('Glass','Paper/Cardboard','Non-Ferrous Metal','Ferrous Metal','Plastics'))
waste_1819 <- waste_1819 %>%
  mutate(recycled = recycled * 1000)

waste_1819 <- waste_1819 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_to_lower(waste_type))

waste_1819 <- waste_1819 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_replace_all(waste_type,"paper/cardboard","paper"))

waste_1819 <- waste_1819 %>%
  mutate(waste_type = str_replace_all(waste_type,'plastics', 'plastic'))

5.3 Energy saved per material

energy_saved <- energy_saved %>%
  select(material,energy_saved)

energy_saved <- energy_saved %>%
  mutate(material = str_to_lower(material)) %>%
  mutate(energy_saved = str_remove(energy_saved, 'Kwh')) %>%
  mutate(energy_saved = str_remove(energy_saved, 'kWh'))


energy_saved
## # A tibble: 5 x 2

6.Join and Calculation

energy_saved$energy_saved <- as.numeric(energy_saved$energy_saved)
total_waste <-  rbind(waste_1517, waste_1819)


total_waste <- total_waste %>%
 left_join(energy_saved, by = c("waste_type"= "material")) 

total_waste <- total_waste %>%
  mutate(total_recycled = energy_saved * recycled)

energy_saved_1519 <-total_waste %>% 
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(total_energy_saved = sum(total_recycled))
